# Data Architecture Rules

Full reference: `data-architecture.md`. This is the enforceable contract.

## STOP and notify on data-architecture changes

Before editing anything that **adds, removes, changes, reshapes, or re-ports
data** — the registries in `src/data.ts`, the `DataSource` seam, the Forge
snapshots/engine (`src/lib/forge/**`), data types in `src/types.ts`, or how data
flows into `AppState` — proactively tell the user:

> "Heads up: this touches the data architecture (`data-architecture.md`). Here's
> what changes and why."

Then keep `data-architecture.md` (and this rule) in sync in the **same** change.
Don't silently restructure data or break the single-source-of-truth / seam
contracts below.

## Single source of truth

- `TICKERS` (company facts) and `PORTFOLIOS[].holdings` (holding facts) in
  `src/data.ts` are authoritative. **Derive, don't duplicate.**
- `INITIAL_WATCHLIST`, `TICKER_ANALYSIS`, `LOG_ENTRIES`, `DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENTS`,
  and `POSITIONS` are **derived** — never hand-edit them; edit the registries.
- Keep derivation transforms (e.g. `watchlistFromHoldings()`) **pure**.
- `ALLOCATIONS`, `RISK_RULES`, `PORTFOLIO_METRICS` are intentionally hand-authored
  literals for now (see the reference doc). Don't "fix" them into derived values
  without explicit instruction — it changes displayed numbers.

## The DataSource seam (`src/lib/datasource/`)

- Components and `AppState` must read **live/portfolio data** through
  `dataSource` (from `../lib/datasource`) — never by importing live-data
  constants (`POSITIONS`, `ALLOCATIONS`, `RISK_RULES`, `PORTFOLIO_METRICS`,
  `MARKET_FLOW`, `TICKER_ANALYSIS`, `PORTFOLIOS`, `INITIAL_WATCHLIST`,
  `LOG_ENTRIES`, `DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENTS`) straight from `src/data.ts`.
- **Static configuration / reference content** (strategy catalog, profile option
  lists, `DEFAULT_CAPTAIN`, education cards, ships/badges, score copy) is NOT
  behind the seam — import it directly from `src/data.ts`.
- Adding a new live-data accessor → add it to the `DataSource` interface AND
  `mockDataSource`.

## Going live

- Swap the single `dataSource` binding in `src/lib/datasource/index.ts` to an
  `ApiDataSource`. Don't scatter API calls into components.
- Async + loading/error and the live-vs-overlay field split land in `AppState`
  only, when the first real API is wired (Pass 2).

## Market Weather (`src/lib/weather/`)

- Scoring (`scoring.ts`) is **pure and provider-agnostic** — feed it normalized
  0–100 sub-scores via `buildReading()`. Don't hand-build readings in the UI.
- Condition metadata (labels, colors, icons, copy) lives ONLY in
  `conditions.ts`; per-condition CSS is `.weather--<id>` / `.weather-bg--<id>`.
- Read weather through `dataSource.getMarketWeather(timeframe)`, never by
  importing `weather/mock.ts` from a component.
- Going live: fetch **one** snapshot per session (premarket/live/afterhours),
  refresh at each session boundary, cache **app-wide** (not per user), and filter
  per user client-side via `TICKERS[ticker].sector`/`.industry`. See
  `data-architecture.md` §5.

## Strategy Forge (`src/lib/forge/`)

- The scoring engine (`scoring.ts`) is **pure, no I/O** — it takes a strategy +
  a `MetricContext` and returns conviction. Display labels come from
  `status.ts` (`resolveStatus`: Layer 1 conviction band + Layer 2 category
  diagnostics → `ResolvedStatus`). Don't fetch or import data inside scoring;
  feed it through `alignment.ts`, which reads the `dataSource` seam.
- Forge inputs come **through the seam**: `getFundamentals`, `getTechnicals`,
  `getMarketContext`, `getBuckets`. A missing metric is `null` ("no data"),
  never a fabricated value. Snapshot values must be **real, sourced** figures
  (last close + latest reported fundamentals) carrying `asOf` + `source`.
- The **metric registry** (`metrics.ts`) is the single source of truth for what
  a chip can test. Add a metric = add to `MetricKey` (`types.ts`) + seed the
  snapshot (`data.ts`) + register in `metrics.ts`. Nothing else.
- Scoring follows the normalized tag/chip/weight algorithm in
  `docs/strategy-forge.md`: active chips (tag-lens union, deduped) → pass/fail
  → rule weights renormalized to 100% of the category → `categoryScore ×
  categoryWeight` summed. **No** thesis/risk gates or conviction clamps.
  Rule weights, tag weights, and category weights each sum to 100;
  `validateStrategy` completeness gates "Apply to Portfolio".
- Conviction is **market-value-weighted** across bucket allocations; a ticker's
  headline = its best-aligned bucket. `AppState` overlays computed
  conviction/status/resolved onto the watchlist — downstream chips (`StatusStack`,
  `PortfolioCompass`) reflect it. "Notify" = in-app chips updating; **no**
  push-notification system.
- Cadence: `technicalsInterval` is clamped **≥ 15m and ≥ `checkInterval`**;
  fundamentals refresh daily and are not user-selectable. See
  `data-architecture.md` §6.

## Safety

- All data is static mock placeholder. Before introducing real/realistic
  personal or financial data, follow `.cursor/rules/security-hardening.mdc`.
